					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/anqxyr" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(966960); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=966960&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227557" alt="anqxyr" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=966960)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/anqxyr" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(966960); return false;" >anqxyr</a></span> <span class="odate time_1336291664 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 May 2012 08:07</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1439623">
									

<p>You know how some articles have quirks, that aren't really necessary for enjoying it, but don't do any harm either. Well, this one have gone and collected all of them, I think - the infohazard warning, that screw ups my userscript-adjusted page formatting btw, dynamic content, hidden messages in white ink, everything.</p>
<p>And normally that would've been a bad thing.</p>
<p>But it still has a good, solid idea at its core, fascinating idea that hadn't been done before, and that's pretty much the only thing that's important. Oh, and it's an infohazard. I <strong>love</strong> infohazards. They are probably the least overdone concept on the wiki. Under my head-canon definition of the term, we only have four of them, including 1231. So, yeah, I am probably a little bit biased here, but I'm upvotig this hard.</p>
<p>Also, the number of thumbnails is displayed with '|' in front of it. I assume that's a typo, but I don't want to change anything so as not to unwittingly brake the counter.</p>
<p>Also also, some of the footnotes seem out of place to me. I would've removed the seventh altogether, since it just repeats what was stated in the article already, and moved the fifth out of footnote into article proper, right before &quot;The videos are not in a time loop,&quot; sentence.</p>

